<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<xsl:stylesheet xmlns="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/shared/base/1/" xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xmlns:comm="http://www.lexis-nexis.com/glp/comm" xmlns:dita="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" xmlns:person="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/shared/person/1/" xmlns:seclaw="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/legal/secondary-law/1/" version="2.0" exclude-result-prefixes="dita">

	<dita:topic xmlns="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="CA10_contrib">
    <title>contrib <lnpid>id-CA10-14610</lnpid></title>

    <body>
        <p>Create a <targetxml>seclaw:prelim/byline</targetxml> and process child element and
            attributes as follows: <ul id="ul_eet_fzc_xj">
                <li><sourcexml>contrib</sourcexml> becomes <targetxml>person:contributor</targetxml>
                    and set <targetxml>@contributor-type='contributor'</targetxml></li>
                <li>drop <sourcexml>@ln.user-displayed</sourcexml></li>
            </ul></p>
        <note>The <targetxml>seclaw:prelim/byline</targetxml> will be a child of the outer-most
            (top-level) occurrence of <targetxml>seclaw:level</targetxml>.</note>
        <p>If <sourcexml>contrib</sourcexml> only contains "&amp;nbsp;" or "&amp;#160;" as shown
            below, do not convert.</p>
        <codeblock>

            &lt;contrib ln.user-displayed="true"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/contrib&gt;
            or
            &lt;contrib ln.user-displayed="true"&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/contrib&gt;

           </codeblock>

        <example>
            <title>Source XML 1</title>
            <codeblock>

&lt;comm:info&gt;
        &lt;contrib ln.user-displayed="true"&gt;Maurice Coombs (Contributor)&lt;/contrib&gt;
        &lt;publication&gt;Halsbury's Laws of Canada - Bills of Exchange&lt;/publication&gt;
    &lt;/comm:info&gt;
    &lt;comm:body&gt;
        &lt;level leveltype="1"&gt;
            &lt;heading align="center"&gt;
                &lt;title&gt;III. PART II OF THE ACT: BILLS OF EXCHANGE&lt;/title&gt;
            &lt;/heading&gt;
            ...

           </codeblock>
            <title>Target XML 1</title>
            <codeblock>

&lt;seclaw:level leveltype="unclassified"&gt;
            &lt;heading align="center"&gt;
                &lt;title&gt;III. PART II OF THE ACT: BILLS OF EXCHANGE&lt;/title&gt;
            &lt;/heading&gt;
            &lt;seclaw:prelim&gt;
                &lt;byline&gt;
                    &lt;person:contributor contributor-type="contributor"&gt;Maurice Coombs
                        (Contributor)&lt;/person:contributor&gt;
                &lt;/byline&gt;
            &lt;/seclaw:prelim&gt;
            ...

           </codeblock>
        </example>
        <example>
            <title>Source XML 2</title>
            <codeblock>

&lt;comm:info&gt;
        &lt;contrib ln.user-displayed="true"&gt;Kevin McGuinness (Main Title Contributor)&lt;/contrib&gt;
        &lt;contrib ln.user-displayed="true"&gt;(Updates prepared by LexisNexis Canada Inc.)&lt;/contrib&gt;
        &lt;publication&gt;Halsbury's Laws of Canada - Business Corporations&lt;/publication&gt;
    &lt;/comm:info&gt;
    &lt;comm:body&gt;
        &lt;level leveltype="3"&gt;
            &lt;heading align="left"&gt;
                &lt;title searchtype="DOC-HEADING"&gt;TABLE OF CASES (A-M)&lt;/title&gt;
            &lt;/heading&gt;
            ...

           </codeblock>
            <title>Target XML 2</title>
            <codeblock>

&lt;seclaw:body&gt;
        &lt;seclaw:level leveltype="unclassified"&gt;
            &lt;heading align="left"&gt;
                &lt;title&gt;TABLE OF CASES (A-M)&lt;/title&gt;
            &lt;/heading&gt;
            &lt;seclaw:prelim&gt;
                &lt;byline&gt;
                    &lt;person:contributor contributor-type="contributor"&gt;Kevin McGuinness (Main Title
                        Contributor)&lt;/person:contributor&gt;
                    &lt;person:contributor contributor-type="contributor"&gt;(Updates prepared by
                        LexisNexis Canada Inc.)&lt;/person:contributor&gt;
                &lt;/byline&gt;
            &lt;/seclaw:prelim&gt;
            ...

           </codeblock>
        </example>
        <section>
            <title>Changes</title>
            <p>2014-05-28: <ph id="change_20140528_jm">Added rule to suppress
                        <sourcexml>contrib</sourcexml> when content is only "&amp;#160;" as already
                    done when content is "&amp;nbsp;". Phase 6 Board Item 112.</ph></p>
        </section>
    </body>
